    "Trained on extensive molecular datasets, they capture essential features and allow for the exploration of new molecular structures.",
    "Challenges in learning encodings include accurately representing chemical space and ensuring relevance to drug development, as molecules close in latent space might have divergent biological and chemical properties.",
    "Access to extensive data is crucial to train algorithms.",
    "Key to this is the availability of public databases.",
    "Prominent among these are ChEMBL (49), PubChem (50), BindingDB (51), and DrugBank (52), which offer essential bioactivity data for drug discovery."
